<text>Inserting a DNA scroller

&lt; Previous | Index | Next &gt;

In Molecular Workbench, proteins are sometimes simplified as a string of beads connected by harmonic spring forces. Each bead represents an amino acid. You can insert a DNA scroller that changes the primary structure of a protein.

Select the &quot;Insert&gt;Special Controller for Model&gt;Proteins and DNA&gt;DNA Scroller&quot; menu. You will see the following dialog box:

  
[This is a screenshot.]

This dialog window allows you to select a protein to control.

Taking a snapshot

To take a snapshot of the DNA scroller, right-click on the space above the scrollbar and below the DNA code, and choose &quot;Take a Snapshot&quot; from the popup menu.

Changing and removing a DNA scroller

See &quot;Editing embedded components&quot; for how to change, move and remove a DNA scroller.

